    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I just made this sauce at Kathryn&#8217;s behest, my favorite friend and cook. In fact, it is still piping hot in the pot on the stove. The blatant subtlety (if you permit me license to juxtapose these two opposing words) of this sauce has no match in my long tenure as a home (and erstwhile professional) cook. However, since I can never leave well enough alone, I was compelled to add alot of salt and just a couple pinches of sugar to those dervish tomatoes and that buttery bulb, since I prefer my sauce on the sweet and savory side. I simply cannot stop licking the wooden spoon. I&#8217;m getting splinters on my tongue. What a deliriously delicious web and blog site this Orangette is!!</p>
