  <li id="comment-7406" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.remedialeating.com" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=1413#comment-7406"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-10-06T01:53:25-04:00">Wednesday, October 6, 2010 at 1:53 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly.  I know this sauce is ancient history, but I must tell you, it made for a revolutionary evening in our home.  </p>
<p>My ten year old son ate sauce on his pasta, tonight.  He has never eaten sauce on his pasta.  As in, never ever.  Plain pasta on the same platter as sauced?  No thanks, he&#39;ll wait until breakfast.  A single parsley flake, spied and removed?  Nix, just water, thanks anyway.  But tonight, he ate pasta with sauce.  This sauce.</p>
<p>I owe you.  Big time.</p>
    </div>

