  <li id="comment-7419" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=1413#comment-7419"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-04-04T03:19:22-04:00">Thursday, April 4, 2013 at 3:19 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>A little late to the party, but I can&#39;t say enough about this sauce, thanks to this blog. Initially, I used the DOP Italian imported tomatoes Whole Foods offers, then tried Costco&#39;s brand of diced tomatoes, and finally, tried Muir Glen&#39;s. I have to say the 4+ dollars I spent on the 28 oz. can of DOP Italian tomatoes was well worth it. The others yielded really good sauce, but the Italian tomatoes were sublime. Somehow, they&#39;re smoother. No matter what&#8211;the sauce is killer good.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=1413#comment-7419' data-commentid="7419" data-postid="1413" data-belowelement="comment-7419" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Anonymous" aria-label='Reply to Anonymous'>Reply</a>    </div>
